#. <section class="sutta" id="sn6.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The Appeal"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 9. Turūbrahmasutta → tudubrahmasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts2) | tudu brahmā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn6.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Turūbrahmasutta"
msgstr "9. With the Brahmā Tudu"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.324"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.9:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn6.9:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena kokāliko bhikkhu ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno."
msgstr "Now at that time the mendicant Kokālika was sick, suffering, gravely ill."

#. VAR: turū → tudu (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn6.9:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho turū paccekabrahmā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena kokāliko bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā vehāsaṃ ṭhito kokālikaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then, late at night, the beautiful independent brahmā Tudu, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the mendicant Kokālika, and standing in the air he said to him:"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn6.9:1.4"
msgid "“pasādehi, kokālika, sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ."
msgstr "“Kokālika, have confidence in Sāriputta and Moggallāna,"

msgctxt "sn6.9:1.5"
msgid "Pesalā sāriputtamoggallānā”ti."
msgstr "they’re good monks.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn6.9:1.6"
msgid "“Kosi tvaṃ, āvuso”ti?"
msgstr "“Who are you, reverend?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn6.9:1.7"
msgid "“Ahaṃ turū paccekabrahmā”ti."
msgstr "“I am Tudu the independent brahmā.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn6.9:1.8"
msgid "“Nanu tvaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā anāgāmī byākato, atha kiñcarahi idhāgato?"
msgstr "“Didn’t the Buddha declare you a non-returner? So what exactly are you doing back here?"

msgctxt "sn6.9:1.9"
msgid "Passa, yāvañca te idaṃ aparaddhan”ti."
msgstr "See how far you have strayed!”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.9:2.1"
msgid "“Purisassa hi jātassa,"
msgstr "“A man is born"

#. <br>
#. VAR: kuṭhārī → kudhārī (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn6.9:2.2"
msgid "kuṭhārī jāyate mukhe;"
msgstr "with an axe in his mouth."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:2.3"
msgid "Yāya chindati attānaṃ,"
msgstr "A fool cuts themselves with it"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:2.4"
msgid "bālo dubbhāsitaṃ bhaṇaṃ."
msgstr "when they say bad words."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.325"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.9:3.1"
msgid "Yo nindiyaṃ pasaṃsati,"
msgstr "When you praise someone worthy of criticism,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ vā nindati yo pasaṃsiyo;"
msgstr "or criticize someone worthy of praise,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:3.3"
msgid "Vicināti mukhena so kaliṃ,"
msgstr "you choose bad luck with your own mouth:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:3.4"
msgid "Kalinā tena sukhaṃ na vindati."
msgstr "you’ll never find happiness that way."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.9:4.1"
msgid "Appamattako ayaṃ kali,"
msgstr "Bad luck at dice is a trivial thing,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:4.2"
msgid "Yo akkhesu dhanaparājayo;"
msgstr "if all you lose is your money"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:4.3"
msgid "Sabbassāpi sahāpi attanā,"
msgstr "and all you own, even yourself."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:4.4"
msgid "Ayameva mahantataro kali;"
msgstr "What’s really terrible luck"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:4.5"
msgid "Yo sugatesu manaṃ padosaye."
msgstr "is to hate the holy ones."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.9:5.1"
msgid "Sataṃ sahassānaṃ nirabbudānaṃ,"
msgstr "For more than two quinquadecillion years,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:5.2"
msgid "Chattiṃsati pañca ca abbudāni;"
msgstr "and another five quattuordecillion years,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Yamariyagarahī → yamariye garahī (s1-3, km) | yamariyaṃ garahaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn6.9:5.3"
msgid "Yamariyagarahī nirayaṃ upeti,"
msgstr "a slanderer of noble ones goes to hell,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.9:5.4"
msgid "Vācaṃ manañca paṇidhāya pāpakan”ti."
msgstr "having aimed bad words and thoughts at them.”"
